Brothers from 300 kilometres away sent emergency supplies.

00:45:27.909 --> 00:45:30.909
The brotherhood showed us love in practice.

00:45:30.909 --> 00:45:34.909
They worked hard and helped us because they loved us.

00:45:34.909 --> 00:45:37.909
I was deeply touched and found myself in awe.

00:45:37.909 --> 00:45:38.909
We are united.

00:45:38.909 --> 00:45:44.909
All of this brought glory and praise to Jehovah.

00:45:44.909 --> 00:45:46.909
When we went there to help,

00:45:46.909 --> 00:45:48.909
the Roman neighbours were very surprised.

00:45:48.909 --> 00:45:50.909
They asked if we could help them too.

00:45:50.909 --> 00:45:54.909
We replied that we have to help our family first.

00:45:55.909 --> 00:45:59.909
They were very puzzled that we called our Roma brothers family

00:45:59.909 --> 00:46:04.250
since we were not from their tribe.

00:46:04.250 --> 00:46:08.250
Ephesians 4.16 finds a good application in this story.

00:46:08.250 --> 00:46:13.250
Just as every joint in the body offers help.

00:46:13.250 --> 00:46:16.250
So did the brothers.

00:46:16.250 --> 00:46:23.300
We all worked together to provide help to our brothers in need.

00:46:23.300 --> 00:46:26.300
Jehovah's teaching me and helping me.

00:46:26.300 --> 00:46:28.300
I really trust in him.

00:46:28.300 --> 00:46:30.300
He has blessed me personally.

00:46:30.300 --> 00:46:33.300
I have seen how good he is to me.

00:46:33.300 --> 00:46:35.300
In a miserable world,

00:46:35.300 --> 00:46:37.300
Jehovah brings me joy.

00:46:37.300 --> 00:46:41.300
I know that he chooses according to a person's heart.

00:46:41.300 --> 00:46:48.869
All glory belongs to Jehovah.

00:46:48.869 --> 00:46:53.869
In total, seven members of the Securus family are studying the Bible.

00:46:53.869 --> 00:46:58.869
Five who are deaf are studying with a Greek sign language group.

00:46:58.869 --> 00:47:02.869
When the flood struck, about 20 people,

00:47:02.869 --> 00:47:04.869
including the Securus family,

00:47:04.869 --> 00:47:07.869
could not be evacuated due to strong currents.

00:47:07.869 --> 00:47:11.869
At first, other Roma, who had been left behind,

00:47:11.869 --> 00:47:16.869
blamed the flood on the family because they were all studying with Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:47:16.869 --> 00:47:21.869
But after they observed the assistance provided by the brothers and sisters,

00:47:21.869 --> 00:47:22.869
they said,

00:47:22.869 --> 00:47:24.869
You have the true religion.

00:47:24.869 --> 00:47:26.869
You show genuine love.

00:47:26.869 --> 00:47:31.730
Our series, My Teen Life,

00:47:31.730 --> 00:47:36.730
has helped many young witnesses navigate today's realities.

00:47:36.730 --> 00:47:41.730
Our next episode has to do with association.

00:47:41.730 --> 00:47:45.730
And we'll hear from a brother and a sister who eventually made good decisions

00:47:45.730 --> 00:47:48.730
with the help of Bible principles.

00:47:48.730 --> 00:47:50.730
That may not surprise you.

00:47:51.730 --> 00:47:55.730
But what we're looking for in this is how.

00:47:55.730 --> 00:48:00.730
How did they go from knowing Bible principles to applying them?

00:48:10.440 --> 00:48:14.440
My parents were both Jehovah's Witnesses by the time I was born.

00:48:14.440 --> 00:48:17.440
So I studied the Bible, attended meetings,

00:48:17.440 --> 00:48:20.440
and went out and surfaced with them.

00:48:20.440 --> 00:48:22.440
Growing up in the truth,

00:48:22.440 --> 00:48:26.440
I knew that living by Bible standards is what's best for me.

00:48:26.440 --> 00:48:30.440
And my parents were always so zealous when it came to spiritual things.

00:48:30.440 --> 00:48:32.440
So when I think back,

00:48:32.440 --> 00:48:36.940
I just didn't want to let them down.

00:48:36.940 --> 00:48:40.940
Following Bible principles is not burdensome or even that difficult.

00:48:40.940 --> 00:48:43.940
Honestly, if we do as it says in the Bible,

00:48:43.940 --> 00:48:46.940
then we benefit ourselves.

00:48:46.940 --> 00:48:52.940
But at times, I was curious how my life would be if I wasn't in the truth.

00:48:52.940 --> 00:48:56.940
It was just so fun to be around my school friends.

00:48:56.940 --> 00:48:59.940
Overall, I had a good time at school.

00:48:59.940 --> 00:49:03.940
I got along with my classmates and my teachers like me too.

00:49:03.940 --> 00:49:06.940
So being in school was a pretty good experience.

00:49:06.940 --> 00:49:11.940
My parents always told me not to get too close to my classmates.

00:49:11.940 --> 00:49:16.940
But in my opinion, my friends had good conduct and were good people.

00:49:16.940 --> 00:49:19.940
I didn't understand why they were so worried.

00:49:19.940 --> 00:49:21.940
In my high school,

00:49:21.940 --> 00:49:24.940
there were a lot of kids who went to church

00:49:24.940 --> 00:49:27.940
and many of the teachers had religious backgrounds.

00:49:27.940 --> 00:49:31.940
One day, there was an incident when the entire school found out

00:49:31.940 --> 00:49:33.940
I was one of Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:49:33.940 --> 00:49:37.940
I knew that some people might be prejudiced against witnesses,

00:49:37.940 --> 00:49:41.940
but I was surprised to see how everyone could change so suddenly.

00:49:41.940 --> 00:49:44.940
I started spending more time with my classmates.

00:49:44.940 --> 00:49:46.940
But the more I hung out with them,

00:49:46.940 --> 00:49:49.940
the more I saw that we were living completely different lives.

00:49:49.940 --> 00:49:53.940
Their conversations would be about trips they went on over the weekend

00:49:53.940 --> 00:49:56.940
and what they bought on their latest shopping trip.

00:49:56.940 --> 00:50:00.940
But when it came to me, all I had done was spiritual activities.

00:50:00.940 --> 00:50:03.940
It felt like I was missing out.

00:50:03.940 --> 00:50:06.940
I felt alone and like an outcast.

00:50:06.940 --> 00:50:11.940
I knew in my head that Bible principles are right and beneficial.

00:50:11.940 --> 00:50:14.940
But when I was actually put in that situation,

00:50:14.940 --> 00:50:18.260
I wasn't so sure anymore.

00:50:18.260 --> 00:50:22.260
I started to feel like I wasn't as cool as my classmates.

00:50:22.260 --> 00:50:25.260
So when they started to talk about their life goals,

00:50:25.260 --> 00:50:29.260
I couldn't bring myself to tell them what my goals were.

00:50:29.260 --> 00:50:31.260
So I started thinking,

00:50:31.260 --> 00:50:34.260
what would be the right way for me to act?

00:50:34.260 --> 00:50:38.260
Opening up to my parents about my situation really helped.

00:50:38.260 --> 00:50:40.260
One day for family worship,

00:50:40.260 --> 00:50:43.260
we decided to discuss that topic.

00:50:43.260 --> 00:50:46.260
We read Matthew chapter 5 verse 11.

00:50:46.260 --> 00:50:50.260
Happy are you when people reproach you and persecute you

00:50:50.260 --> 00:50:55.260
and blindly say every sort of wicked thing against you for my sake.

00:50:55.260 --> 00:50:58.260
But how can you be happy when persecuted?

00:50:58.260 --> 00:51:00.260
I thought to myself,

00:51:00.260 --> 00:51:02.260
but I'm not happy right now.

00:51:02.260 --> 00:51:05.260
My mom shared Mark 838 with me.

00:51:05.260 --> 00:51:07.260
The part in the scripture where it says that,

00:51:07.260 --> 00:51:09.260
if we are ashamed of Jesus Christ,

00:51:09.260 --> 00:51:11.260
He will be ashamed of us.

00:51:11.260 --> 00:51:13.260
Really hit me.

00:51:13.260 --> 00:51:15.260
I realized that deep inside,

00:51:15.260 --> 00:51:18.260
I had been ashamed of being a witness.

00:51:18.260 --> 00:51:20.260
While I was going through all of this,

00:51:20.260 --> 00:51:23.260
a brother gave a public talk in a congregation

00:51:23.260 --> 00:51:26.260
and read Matthew chapter 19 verse 29.

00:51:26.260 --> 00:51:27.260
There it says,

00:51:27.260 --> 00:51:30.260
that everyone who has left what is important to them

00:51:30.260 --> 00:51:35.260
for the sake of Jehovah will receive a hundred times as much.

00:51:35.260 --> 00:51:39.260
So I decided to try living what I thought was important to me

00:51:39.260 --> 00:51:42.260
and see what results and blessings I might receive.

00:51:42.260 --> 00:51:44.260
About that time,

00:51:44.260 --> 00:51:47.260
my parents helped me to associate with brothers and sisters

00:51:47.260 --> 00:51:51.260
who were participating in many different forms of full-time service

00:51:51.260 --> 00:51:54.260
so that I could hear their experiences.

00:51:54.260 --> 00:51:59.260
That helped me to decide which direction I wanted to go in my life.

00:51:59.260 --> 00:52:02.260
One thing that was really great about this decision

00:52:02.260 --> 00:52:06.260
was that I was able to meet many new brothers and sisters.

00:52:06.260 --> 00:52:08.260
I realized that there were so many people

00:52:08.260 --> 00:52:11.260
who had the same thoughts and goals as I did.

00:52:11.260 --> 00:52:14.260
These were my true friends.

00:52:14.260 --> 00:52:18.260
The next time the topic of our future goals came up with my classmates,

00:52:18.260 --> 00:52:20.260
I was able to speak up confidently.

00:52:20.260 --> 00:52:25.260
I am really thankful to my parents who helped me to find the courage to do that.

00:52:25.260 --> 00:52:29.260
I felt that Jehovah truly keeps his promises.

00:52:29.260 --> 00:52:31.260
Come to think of it,

00:52:31.260 --> 00:52:35.260
Jehovah has kept his promise to reward me a hundred times as much

00:52:35.260 --> 00:52:39.260
if I choose to live by the Bible's principles.

00:52:39.260 --> 00:52:43.500
I am really happy now

00:52:43.500 --> 00:52:47.500
when I am confident that if I follow the Bible's teachings when I make decisions,

00:52:47.500 --> 00:52:51.500
I will always have the best results.

00:52:51.500 --> 00:53:06.699
They were familiar with the Bible,

00:53:06.699 --> 00:53:09.699
but its value became real to them

00:53:09.699 --> 00:53:13.699
when they put Bible principles into practice.

00:53:13.699 --> 00:53:19.650
This month's program underscored that in difficult times,

00:53:19.650 --> 00:53:23.650
Jehovah always comforts.

00:53:23.650 --> 00:53:27.650
Servants of Jehovah like Sister Brown and her daughter

00:53:27.650 --> 00:53:30.650
may suffer terrible blows,

00:53:30.650 --> 00:53:32.650
but no matter what happens to us,

00:53:32.650 --> 00:53:34.650
even if we die,

00:53:34.650 --> 00:53:37.650
we always belong to Jehovah.

00:53:37.650 --> 00:53:40.650
Bible truths were a comfort to my own bee

00:53:40.650 --> 00:53:43.650
who never gave up searching for God.

00:53:43.650 --> 00:53:45.650
And finally,

00:53:45.650 --> 00:53:50.650
all of us provide comfort when we show impartial love.

